definition.message:
A health score is a heuristic generated by Cisco ACI to represent the state of a leaf or spine node. It provides a high level understanding if something isn't in a good shape. For example, a spine with 6 power supplies that has 1 power supply failure isn't going to lower it's health score as much as a leaf switch with two power supplies that loses one.

{{#is_alert}}
{{node_id.name}} in namespace {{device_namespace.name}} is reporting low health score (under 50%).
{{/is_alert}}

{{#is_warning}}
{{node_id.name}} in namespace {{device_namespace.name}} is reporting lower health score (under 90%).
{{/is_warning}} 

{{#is_recovery}}
{{node_id.name}} in namespace {{device_namespace.name}} is reporting healthy score (over 90%).
{{/is_recovery}}
